  @{b}ver. 1.0@{ub}  - the first version

@endnode


@node INST "Installation"

    @{FG shine}- Installation -@{FG text}

  @{u}@{b}IMPORTANT@{ub}@{uu}: if you already have a precedent version of YamExpansion don't worry,
 it will not interfere with this version. You can leave it, test this new version and
 if you prefere the new one then delete the old YamExpansion and remove also the
 @{b}yamexpansion:@{ub} assignment.

  First of all double-click on the @{b}InstallEng@{ub} icon in this drawer. Follow
 the instructions and you'll install all the program in a drawer.

  After that you can start the program double-clicking on the @{b}YAMExpansion@{ub}
 icon in the @{b}yamexp:@{ub} directory. But if you want, you can add a menu item
 in the @{FG shine}Yam@{FG text} @{b}Scripts@{ub} menu. To make so:

  in @{FG shine}Yam@{FG text}, open @{b}Settings@{ub} - @{b}Configuration@{ub}, go to the @{b}ARexx@{ub} section where you will
 find all the @{b}'Scripts' menu entry @{FG shine}x@{FG text}@{ub}.

  Select a free one and write @{i}YamExpansion@{ui} as Name, @{i}AmigaDOS@{ui} as script type (it's the
 cycle gadget on the right of Name), and, below, @{i}yamexp:yamexpansion@{ui} as Script. Leave @{i}Open
 console window@{ui} and @{i}Wait for termination@{ui} @{u}unset@{uu}.

  If all the @{b}'Scripts' menu entry@{ub}s are full then the only thing to do is to substitute a
 script that you don't use often.

  You can also autostart YamExpansion when you read an Aminet recent email, to make so:

  in @{FG shine}Yam@{FG text}, open @{b}Settings@{ub} - @{b}Configuration@{ub}, go to the @{b}ARexx@{ub} section where you will
 find the @{b}When reading a message@{ub} entry and select it. Now set the cycle gadget on @{b}ARexx@{ub} and
 write @{b}Rexx/AutoYamExp.rexx @{ub}as @{b}Script@{ub}, leave unset the @{b}Open console window@{ub}
 and @{b}Wait for termination@{ub} options. That's all, now when you are reading emails and
 you meet a recent one, then Yam will open YamExpansion automatically.

@endnode



